WEBVTT

00:02.146 --> 00:08.413
Christ, mercy and peace be unto you from our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ, again, a portion of the Epistle reading assigned for today.

00:08.453 --> 00:27.955
In Him, Jesus Christ, we have redemption through His blood, the forgiveness of our trespasses according to the rich of His grace, which He lavished upon us, in all wisdom and insight making known to us the mystery of His will, according to His purpose, which He set forth in Christ.

00:29.116 --> 00:30.578
You'll join me with the word of prayer.

00:32.834 --> 00:58.442
Lord, God Heavenly Father, as we gather on this day, we ask that You would lead us to be people of wonder, people who reflect on and consider and spend time in this good news that we have received and heard this season, the good news of a child who has been born, and the one who would receive all of these great and noble titles, wonderful counselor and mighty God, prince of peace and everlasting Father.

00:58.502 --> 01:02.066
Lord, let us to see Him as He is, the Son who was sent from heaven

01:02.498 --> 01:03.319
to be our Savior.

01:04.080 --> 01:08.886
Let us receive Him, reflect on Him, and spend time in His presence once again.

01:08.926 --> 01:10.068
We pray now in Jesus' name.

01:10.729 --> 01:10.989
Amen.

01:11.850 --> 01:12.771
The congregation may be seated.

01:12.811 --> 01:23.125
This is about the time of year, a week or two after Christmas, that I like to ask our kids.

01:24.166 --> 01:25.728
Do you remember all the things you got for Christmas?

01:26.690 --> 01:29.213
Do you remember all the presents that you got?

01:29.253 --> 01:30.034
Can you name them?

01:31.906 --> 01:37.133
Because maybe they'll get a couple, but I'm sure they would miss a few already by this time.

01:37.193 --> 01:38.614
So how about you?

01:38.634 --> 01:40.317
Do you remember all the things you got for Christmas?

01:40.637 --> 01:52.071
If you got a few things for Christmas, maybe helpful for us to consider and remember the difference between those things that last and those things that don't.

01:52.812 --> 02:00.562
The things that are fleeting in this world, which so many things are, and then the things that are eternal.

02:01.122 --> 02:24.757
That's what we were really invited to see and consider this season, Jesus Christ, the one who's prophesied in Isaiah chapter nine called eternal father, almighty God, the one who would come and rule and would rule eternally forever with a kingdom that does not end, which is so different from every single thing in this world, everything else.

02:25.798 --> 02:31.026
And though we are tempted to put our hope and our trust in things of this world, whether it be

02:31.298 --> 02:40.669
the presence we're waiting for on Christmas morning, or money saved up in a bank account, or the people that we find joy in around us.

02:41.550 --> 02:48.859
We know that everything in this life is temporary and fleeting, but his promises are eternal.

02:50.181 --> 02:51.623
His promise is given to us as people.

02:51.963 --> 03:01.074
So today we're invited to come and once again and see and hear and rejoice and celebrate in this good news that has been given to us and the hymn that we just sang

03:01.890 --> 03:05.034
Verse four, oh ye heights of heaven adore him.

03:05.695 --> 03:07.958
Angel hosts his praises sing.

03:07.998 --> 03:12.604
Powers, dominions, bow before him and extol our God and King.

03:13.045 --> 03:17.951
Let no tongue on earth be silent every voice in concert ring.

03:18.011 --> 03:21.556
This is what we are invited to do this season.

03:23.098 --> 03:28.946
To raise our voices with the voices of the angels and the powers on high, the heavenly dominion,

03:29.058 --> 03:33.605
All of these, we're raising our voices with them, rejoicing at the Savior who has come.

03:34.906 --> 03:39.853
The long-promised King who is here with us, and we are invited to receive him this season.

03:41.396 --> 03:43.499
This morning for a few minutes, I want to reflect again.

03:43.559 --> 03:51.570
We have this amazing passage in the book of Ephesians that tells us the meaning and significance of all that Jesus has done.

03:51.590 --> 03:56.978
And as we receive it, I'd like to consider for a few minutes this morning how we respond.

03:57.954 --> 03:59.998
How do we respond to this good news?

04:00.078 --> 04:05.929
How do we not just receive it and hold it and consider it, but also how do we respond to it?

04:06.931 --> 04:07.973
That's where we'll go this morning.

04:09.696 --> 04:18.913
We see here in Ephesians chapter 1, the explanation of the meaning of what this significance is, of what Christ has done for us.

04:18.973 --> 04:21.458
And it's huge, it's magnitudes.

04:22.018 --> 04:29.065
It's weighty, it's glorious, it's holy, it's all these things because these are promises that are given to us that change our lives and change the world.

04:30.586 --> 04:32.628
And though yes, we are people who are waiting still.

04:34.050 --> 04:50.866
Some of this we can't see yet because we look to the day that is to come, the coming of Christ once again, when He will set all things straight, when all powers will truly rest under His authority in an eternal sort of way and when it will be made clear to us that He is the true King on the throne.

04:52.066 --> 04:55.109
Yet even now we receive these promises and we know it's true for us.

04:55.730 --> 05:01.075
His salvation has come and its forgiveness has come and so at verse seven we find in him we have redemption through his blood.

05:01.655 --> 05:06.760
The forgiveness of our trespasses according to the rich of his grace which he lavishes upon us.

05:08.122 --> 05:15.949
In all wisdom and insight making known to us the mystery of his will according to his purpose which set forth in Christ as a plan for the fullness of time.

05:15.969 --> 05:20.594
A summary here in Ephesians chapter one of what God has done

05:20.962 --> 05:22.483
creating a plan of salvation.

05:22.544 --> 05:34.315
From the very foundations of the world, from the moment that humankind fell into sin, from the moment that sin entered into this world, God was preparing a plan of salvation.

05:35.456 --> 05:46.627
Was already putting into work the steps that were needed in order for his own son, his very being to come into this world and even as a child.

05:48.869 --> 05:49.970
And as he comes,

05:50.114 --> 05:51.636
accomplishes all of these things.

05:52.797 --> 05:54.940
He accomplishes the forgiveness of our trespasses.

05:54.960 --> 05:56.482
He takes our sins upon himself.

05:57.063 --> 05:59.125
He goes to the cross for the forgiveness of our sins.

05:59.145 --> 06:00.327
He sheds his own blood.

06:01.188 --> 06:02.770
He conquers death.

06:04.913 --> 06:14.164
The very greatest of the curses which were placed upon Adam and Eve in the garden that they would face death, that they would die and would not live, that their lives would end.

06:15.806 --> 06:18.610
And this promise Jesus overcomes.

06:19.714 --> 06:24.200
He overcomes in his glory and his greatness and his humility and his sacrifice.

06:24.220 --> 06:27.884
He goes to the cross overcoming death and rising again on the third day.

06:27.924 --> 06:34.993
Amazing to think though as we do during the season that he came as a child and as an infant.

06:35.053 --> 06:36.215
This is how we receive him.

06:36.255 --> 06:38.297
This is how Mary and Joseph received him.

06:38.317 --> 06:40.300
He came as an infant.

06:40.920 --> 06:48.690
All the glory of God, all the majesty of God, all the truth of God who was the true king, the wisdom of God as we hear in these other

06:49.026 --> 06:53.433
readings that the true wisdom of God shall come into the world.

06:54.695 --> 07:10.679
And he comes as an infant, as one who could be held, as one who needed assistance from his parents, as it says in the gospel reading this morning, he rested under their authority.

07:11.260 --> 07:12.381
He left the temple that day.

07:12.441 --> 07:16.848
He came back and he was subservient to them as an infant.

07:16.868 --> 07:18.130
He was as well.

07:19.298 --> 07:27.948
Dorothy Sayers puts it like this, the incarnation means that for whatever reason God chose to let us fall to suffer and to be subject to the sorrows and death.

07:28.869 --> 07:32.373
He has nonetheless had the honesty and the courage to take his own medicine.

07:33.395 --> 07:36.218
He can exact nothing from man that he has not exacted from himself.

07:36.338 --> 07:46.450
He himself has gone through the whole of human experience from the trivial, irrational, irritations of family life and the cramping restrictions of hard work and lack of money

07:46.978 --> 07:51.724
to the worst horrors of pain and humiliation, defeat, despair, and death.

07:52.345 --> 07:56.771
He was born in poverty and suffered infinite pain, all for us.

07:57.813 --> 07:59.855
And he thought it well worth his while.

08:01.678 --> 08:07.666
He willingly endured the human condition as what this means, and as an infant.

08:08.930 --> 08:20.242
I can remember the wonder and mystery of bringing our first child home from the hospital and all the anxiety that was there with going through that process because it is an anxious time bringing a child into the world.

08:20.883 --> 08:25.548
And you wouldn't know it now but she was born on the smaller side and so the doctors and nurses encouraged us.

08:25.568 --> 08:30.774
We need to make sure she's getting enough to eat because her weight dropped in those first few days after being born.

08:30.834 --> 08:33.978
So we had a little nervousness about all of that.

08:34.338 --> 08:38.002
Hopefully the weight gain will come and it did over time.

08:39.522 --> 08:46.890
But you see all of the meekness, all of the tenderness, all of the need that's wrapped up in an infant.

08:48.772 --> 08:57.702
Truly helpless, relying on others to give everything that is needed and the fact that Jesus came into the world in this way.

08:58.282 --> 09:08.914
The fact that God dwelt in an infant born into this world through this gift given to Mary who willingly became a servant of this process.

09:10.050 --> 09:15.137
and God in all humility dwelt among us in that way.

09:16.358 --> 09:31.439
It's still amazing to consider that the glory of God, the holiness of God, the righteousness of God, the justice of God, all of those properties and characteristics which God holds somehow dwelt in an infant and a child who was born in a very lowly way.

09:33.281 --> 09:40.050
And as Dorothy sayers, he thought it was all well worth his while out of love for us, his people.

09:41.378 --> 09:45.043
So now to consider for just a moment this morning, how do we respond?

09:45.664 --> 09:47.647
How do we respond to this gift that is given?

09:47.727 --> 09:51.152
Certainly we bring them our praise, our worship, our lives.

09:52.093 --> 10:01.266
But a couple of things that Mary herself does, as she hears this promise given to her, some scholars have called Mary the first Christian, the first

10:01.378 --> 10:05.482
Christian to have faith in this child because the promise was given to her first.

10:05.843 --> 10:09.006
She saw this come forth into her life and then into the world.

10:09.106 --> 10:11.369
She could be considered the very first Christian.

10:11.689 --> 10:13.011
So how does Mary respond?

10:13.071 --> 10:18.156
Because she offers to us a wonderful model to responding to these things.

10:18.256 --> 10:21.240
First, faithful questioning.

10:22.841 --> 10:24.123
We can do this in our lives as well.

10:24.883 --> 10:25.344
And we ought to.

10:25.404 --> 10:27.006
This could be also called studying.

10:27.026 --> 10:29.308
It could be called reflecting on the Word of God.

10:29.328 --> 10:30.930
It could be called considering

10:31.074 --> 10:36.302
pondering, wondering at these things that God has done, faithful questioning.

10:36.362 --> 10:41.850
Because when the angel comes to her, she says, how will this be?

10:41.910 --> 10:45.515
Seeing that I have known not a man.

10:45.555 --> 10:47.999
This is Mary's question to the angel.

10:48.079 --> 10:49.000
How shall this be?

10:49.040 --> 10:52.646
Amazingly, though, she's not chastised.

10:54.108 --> 10:55.730
You remember the story of Zachariah?

10:56.130 --> 11:01.519
When he also is met by an angel, he goes into the temple, he's ready to perform his priestly duties.

11:02.201 --> 11:07.730
He's told that he also will receive the gift of a child, him and Elizabeth.

11:09.173 --> 11:12.919
But he responds with a question, whereby shall I know this?

11:12.999 --> 11:14.622
I'm using the King James version here.

11:14.963 --> 11:16.205
Whereby shall I know this for?

11:16.225 --> 11:19.250
And I am an old man and my wife, well stricken in years.

11:19.650 --> 11:28.462
And the angel answered and said unto him, I am Gabriel that stand in the presence of God, and am I sent to speak unto thee and to show thee these glad tidings?

11:29.804 --> 11:32.808
And then shortly thereafter, Zachariah was struck mute.

11:34.951 --> 11:36.894
He essentially argued with an angel.

11:39.177 --> 11:43.383
He asked his question, how can this be because we are old in age?

11:44.444 --> 11:45.906
Gabriel chastises him.

11:46.818 --> 11:49.181
Interestingly though, the same thing does not happen for Mary.

11:49.201 --> 11:51.244
Mary is not struck mute.

11:51.344 --> 11:55.609
She asked a question of the angel, also, how shall this be since I have known not a man?

11:56.330 --> 11:57.792
So what is the difference between these two?

11:59.334 --> 12:02.078
Maybe it is faithful questioning.

12:02.458 --> 12:08.166
Certainly the angel could have known what's going on in their hearts could be directed by God at how to respond to these things.

12:08.226 --> 12:14.514
But we get the idea that Zachariah responds with doubt to the angel's proclamation.

12:15.362 --> 12:29.618
that his question doesn't come from a place of a faithful response or a trust, but rather a seed of doubt that's there in Zachariah's heart and mind as he receives this promise and he comes up with reasons why this can't be, we are old and age, don't you know?

12:29.678 --> 12:31.720
Don't you know our age?

12:33.081 --> 12:33.982
How can these things be?

12:34.062 --> 12:35.464
This isn't possible for us.

12:36.665 --> 12:40.610
And so Zachariah is struck mute by the angel.

12:42.171 --> 12:44.594
But Mary's question, I think we could call faithful

12:44.674 --> 12:48.559
Questioning, she says to the angel, how shall this be since I have no not a man?

12:49.059 --> 12:54.085
The angel answered and said to her, the Holy Ghost shall come upon thee and the power of the highest shall overshadow thee.

12:54.486 --> 12:58.470
Therefore also that holy thing which shall be born of thee shall be called the Son of God."

12:59.872 --> 13:11.506
And then Mary says a few verses later, behold, the handmaid of the Lord, be it unto me according to thy word and the angel departed from her.

13:13.122 --> 13:16.290
This is her response, a question, how can this be?

13:16.330 --> 13:17.252
How will this be?

13:17.292 --> 13:18.415
How will this take place?

13:18.896 --> 13:22.124
And then the response, behold, I am the handmaid of the Lord.

13:22.164 --> 13:23.627
Be it unto me according to thy word."

13:25.091 --> 13:26.253
And the angel departed from her.

13:27.015 --> 13:28.178
Faithful questioning.

13:29.154 --> 13:40.271
I do believe this is part of our Christian lives and we started with early on with Sunday school education and teaching our children to ask questions and to explore, to work through scripture and to read for themselves.

13:40.631 --> 13:44.277
And then we go through the process of confirmation where we invite them.

13:45.659 --> 13:55.794
Come forward with your questions, learn more for yourself, process your faith, confirm it and take it into your own hearts so that you too can know and hold this faith as your own.

13:56.738 --> 14:01.405
Faithful questioning, but not a questioning that says these things cannot be possible for God.

14:02.646 --> 14:07.293
But if these things are possible, then help me to see them also.

14:07.333 --> 14:10.678
Faithful questioning our response.

14:10.738 --> 14:17.688
Faithful questioning, as Mary questioned, was bold to question the angel, how shall these things take place?

14:17.888 --> 14:24.978
And then in her response, behold, the handmaid of the Lord and be it unto me according to thy word, I am thy servant.

14:25.890 --> 14:30.916
So number one, faithful questioning and number two, thoughtful pondering.

14:32.237 --> 14:33.279
I'll ask one more question.

14:34.380 --> 14:38.084
Have you made time to ponder these things this season?

14:39.165 --> 14:52.160
It's the invitation of Advent is to await, to be patient, to make time, to come and see, to slow down, to look, to anticipate and expect all that God is doing our midst.

14:52.180 --> 14:53.682
But of course, as I've said earlier,

14:54.690 --> 14:57.553
This comes for us at the busiest time of the year.

14:58.734 --> 15:08.443
We have all of these lists on our calendars leading up to that big day, and so it may chase out any time that we have for thoughtful pondering.

15:09.765 --> 15:11.627
But this is the other response of Mary.

15:11.947 --> 15:17.012
Faithful questioning, but then thoughtful pondering, she reflects on several different occasions.

15:17.572 --> 15:23.378
In Luke 2, verse 19, it says, Mary kept all these things, and she pondered them.

15:24.354 --> 15:24.935
in her heart.

15:26.737 --> 15:34.986
Earlier in chapter one, she says, my soul magnifies the Lord and my spirit hath rejoiced in God my Savior.

15:35.427 --> 15:42.875
My soul magnifies the Lord means to make great, means to compound and elevate and consider and look into.

15:44.537 --> 15:48.422
Mary kept all these things and she pondered them in her heart.

15:50.524 --> 15:52.146
For us as well, this is

15:52.706 --> 16:01.059
a gift we are invited to receive with pondering and with wonder, to look in and to see.

16:01.099 --> 16:09.231
We're told that even the angels long to see the gospel long to look into these same promises that God has given to us.

16:11.455 --> 16:18.706
So how are you doing at pondering, that considering, at reflecting on, at stepping into, at looking at, and exploring

16:19.746 --> 16:26.717
these promises that have been made to known to us, that have been given to us in a personal way that we are invited now to receive.

16:27.919 --> 16:31.424
That word ponder in Greek, is symbolusa.

16:32.766 --> 16:41.921
And it means actually to have a conversation, or at least that's one way it can be translated, sometimes pondering, sometimes conversing, or even to helper to meet.

16:43.303 --> 16:44.505
But think about that for a moment.

16:45.787 --> 16:47.890
A conversation within ourselves.

16:48.802 --> 16:50.263
Seems to be what Mary is doing.

16:50.404 --> 16:58.612
She sees first the gifts of God given to her that a child has come that all the promises of God are somehow wrapped up in this child.

16:58.872 --> 17:01.174
This infant that she is now invited to take care of.

17:01.595 --> 17:03.657
And then she steps back and she ponders.

17:05.318 --> 17:05.879
She looks.

17:06.099 --> 17:07.060
She treasures up.

17:07.140 --> 17:07.921
She receives.

17:08.141 --> 17:08.962
She holds.

17:10.123 --> 17:17.170
And she considers she has a conversation within herself within her heart and mind of what all of this means.

17:18.754 --> 17:21.537
And we too are invited to consider and to reflect.

17:22.638 --> 17:25.201
So I'll give you that invitation one more time again today.

17:25.221 --> 17:48.146
To faithful questioning, to seeing and exploring the promises of God, and how they are true for us, how they are made known to us, and how we are invited to come and look and see, and then thoughtful pondering, to reflect, to take time, to sit and wonder at the good things that God has done, and Jesus Christ our Lord, the very one,

17:49.250 --> 17:59.144
who has come to give us redemption through his blood, the forgiveness of our trespasses, according to the rich of his grace, which he has lavished upon us.

18:00.566 --> 18:03.730
All of this, out of his love, for us is his people.

18:04.531 --> 18:05.753
So let us give thanks this day.

18:05.993 --> 18:06.855
We pray in Jesus' name.

18:07.556 --> 18:07.836
Amen.

18:09.679 --> 18:10.760
And by the congregation, to stand.

18:12.322 --> 18:16.668
And by the peace of God, which passes all understanding, keep our hearts and minds in Christ, Jesus our Lord.

18:17.429 --> 18:17.810
Amen.

